msgstr ""
"从网络安装\n"
"\n"
"== Introduction\n"
"\n"
"When it comes to installing software on your computer, you have a few different options. One of these options is installing from the network. This means that instead of downloading the software to your computer and then installing it from there, you can directly install the software from a server on the network.\n"
"\n"
"== Procedure\n"
"\n"
"To install software from the network, follow these steps:\n"
"\n"
"1. Connect your computer to the network.\n"
"\n"
"2. Open the software management tool on your computer. This may be called \"Software Center\" or \"Package Manager.\"\n"
"\n"
"3. Search for the software you want to install in the software management tool. You can use keywords to help narrow down the search results.\n"
"\n"
"4. Once you have found the software you want to install, select it and click the \"Install\" button.\n"
"\n"
"5. The software management tool will download the necessary files from the server and install the software on your computer.\n"
"\n"
"6. Once the installation is complete, you can start using the software.\n"
"\n"
"== Conclusion\n"
"\n"
"Installing software from the network can be a convenient way to quickly and easily install new applications on your computer. By following the steps outlined above, you can install software from a server on your network and start using it in no time."

